President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Mississippi due to severe winter storms that occurred from February 11 to February 19, 2021. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Brett H. Howard has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future if requested by the state and warranted by further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.